Rabies -- ferret badger
-----------------------
Information received on [and dated] 11 Dec 2013 from Dr Ping-Cheng Yang, director, Animal Technology Institute Taiwan, Council of Agriculture, Taiwan, Chinese Taipei

Summary
Report type: follow-up report No. 44
Start date: 23 May 2012
Date of pre-confirmation of the event: 24 Jun 2013
Reason for notification: reoccurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence: 8 Mar 1959
Manifestation of disease: clinical disease
Causal agent: Lyssavirus
Nature of diagnosis: laboratory (basic and advanced)
This event pertains to a defined zone within the country

New outbreaks
Outbreak 1, Chenggong Township, Taitung County
Date of start of the outbreak: 26 Nov 2013
Outbreak status: resolved (30 Nov 2013)
Epidemiological unit: not applicable
Population type: wild
Affected animals
Species: Chinese ferret-badger: _Melogale moschata_ (Mustelidae)
Cases 1; deaths 1

