Epidemiological comments
The Animal Health Research Institute (National laboratory) has confirmed rabies virus infection by direct fluorescent antibody test in 8 ferret-badgers which were found in Nantou County, Taichung City and Taitung County. The prefectural competent authorities have been conducting intensified vaccination activities targeted at dogs and cats in the areas where infected ferret-badgers were found. Monitoring is ongoing.

Control measures applied
Quarantine
Screening
Vaccination in response to the outbreak (s)
No treatment of affected animals

Diagnostic test results
Animal Health Research Institute (National laboratory), Chinese Ferret-badger, direct fluorescent antibody (FAT) test, 4 Dec 2013, positive
Animal Health Research Institute (National laboratory), Chinese Ferret-badger, direct fluorescent antibody (FAT) test, 9 Dec 2013, positive

The event is continuing. Weekly follow-up reports will be submitted.

[The location of the outbreaks can be seen on the interactive map included in the OIE report at the source URL above.]

